The paper deals with the problem of answering queries subject to differential privacy, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the efficiency of differentially private mechanisms, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper uses statistical and search queries, which are common in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper also discusses information theory and the trade-off between privacy and utility (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with databases and data management, as it considers the problem of answering queries about a dataset (cs.DB).
